and onto another boat.

16:39.240 --> 16:40.520
Do you understand?

16:43.560 --> 16:44.840
Yeah.

16:56.200 --> 16:58.680
The doctor from the Sanatorium
called and said that he needs

16:58.680 --> 17:00.640
to speak to you urgently.

17:02.800 --> 17:05.920
But I think now you are beyond
the help of doctors. Lizzie...

17:09.480 --> 17:11.160
Frances said Arthur's here.

17:43.880 --> 17:45.000
Tommy?

17:46.920 --> 17:48.520
Tom? Yeah, it's me.

17:50.040 --> 17:51.160
Ah, fuck.

18:10.760 --> 18:12.400
Arthur, give me a light, will you?

18:13.440 --> 18:14.800
I can't find my lighter.

18:16.320 --> 18:17.920
HE EXHALES SHARPLY

18:27.240 --> 18:29.640
I'm sorry I couldn't speak at the
wagon, Tom.

18:40.120 --> 18:41.360
Don't be sorry.

18:44.520 --> 18:45.960
What are you doing here?

18:49.320 --> 18:52.000
Waiting for this fucking cup
to fill up.

18:56.080 --> 18:57.640
Nearly empty, this barrel.

18:59.360 --> 19:00.920
There are plenty of barrels, Arthur.

19:02.400 --> 19:04.480
Start another barrel.

19:04.480 --> 19:07.000
I thought maybe they're all full
of fucking blood.

19:11.000 --> 19:12.600
The junk, Tom...

19:14.560 --> 19:16.160
..fucks you up your mind.

19:20.560 --> 19:21.960
You know, Arthur.

19:24.400 --> 19:26.200
You was already fucked up.

19:28.600 --> 19:31.520
You was fucked up since you
were a kid.

19:33.520 --> 19:34.880
This is my theory.

19:38.840 --> 19:40.600
It's from that time I gave you

19:40.600 --> 19:43.080
a beating when you were 12
and I was nine.

19:44.520 --> 19:46.320
We were fighting over cigarettes.

19:48.880 --> 19:53.840
Maybe when I had you down
on the ground,

19:53.840 --> 19:56.960
I gave you one too many to
the head.

19:56.960 --> 19:59.760
It was a draw, though, Tom.

19:59.760 --> 20:02.760
Nah, I beat you.

20:04.200 --> 20:07.320
I had you pinned.
You actually didn't.

20:09.360 --> 20:13.320
We both agreed. You're so fucked,
you can't remember, brother.

20:15.280 --> 20:18.680
I do. I do remember little things.

20:18.680 --> 20:20.240
I know you do.

20:21.400 --> 20:22.680
So, do I.

20:23.880 --> 20:25.680
The fog and the gas is clearing, eh?

20:37.960 --> 20:39.280
TOMMY COUGHS

21:17.960 --> 21:20.280
Here, that cup's nearly full.
Pass it here.

21:24.560 --> 21:25.720
That's...

21:28.560 --> 21:30.480
Tommy...stuff any more.

21:32.840 --> 21:34.920
You don't drink no more, Tom.

21:58.440 --> 22:00.880
After Polly was gone, Arthur...

22:02.200 --> 22:04.160
..I thought I could just march
and march.

22:05.560 --> 22:07.360
I just kept up that fucking left,

22:07.360 --> 22:09.960
right, left, right, left, right,
fucking rhythm.

22:11.240 --> 22:12.720
I'd never have to stop.

22:15.440 --> 22:16.960
Then Ruby went.

22:20.880 --> 22:22.360
I stumbled and crashed.

22:28.120 --> 22:29.720
And now here I am...

22:31.440 --> 22:36.240
..sat on my arse on the ground

22:36.240 --> 22:38.440
like a fucking tunneller..

22:40.640 --> 22:42.800
..with my old comrade Arthur.

22:47.640 --> 22:49.280
Remember the January, Arthur?

22:51.920 --> 22:53.160
The family boat?

22:54.920 --> 22:56.720
The whole family living on something

22:56.720 --> 22:59.000
the size of ten of these
fucking barrels.

23:02.720 --> 23:07.000
Remember that night at Tile Cross,

23:07.000 --> 23:10.440
16 of us sleeping on the boat,
the coppers come.

23:11.760 --> 23:13.240
We all swam like rats.

23:14.240 --> 23:16.080
Except for Arthur.

23:16.080 --> 23:20.840
Arthur holds them off with
a boat hook, all on his own.

23:22.800 --> 23:24.880
And I remember,

23:24.880 --> 23:27.480
I climbed back up at the lock
and looked back

23:27.480 --> 23:30.600
and saw you waving that
fucking boat hook

23:30.600 --> 23:33.640
in the copper's faces...
ARTHUR CHUCKLES

23:33.640 --> 23:34.880
..on your own.

23:36.240 --> 23:37.760
That's when I realised.

23:39.640 --> 23:44.200
When I had you on the ground,
all them years ago,

23:44.200 --> 23:46.360
it's because you let me win.

23:49.920 --> 23:51.720
You wanted me to win.

23:55.600 --> 23:57.800
you've wanted me to win ever since.

24:00.080 --> 24:06.720
What chance do I have...if you start
doing that again, eh?

24:08.680 --> 24:10.920
You'll stop.

24:10.920 --> 24:14.000
You'll stop cos the family
needs you to.

24:15.400 --> 24:17.760
It's like that long tunnel
on the Dudley stretch.

24:18.920 --> 24:20.800
You remember Dudley canal,
line number one?

24:20.800 --> 24:25.760
3,172 yards of fucking
pitch blackness and rats swimming.

24:25.760 --> 24:28.320
Yeah. Then we'd come round that
corner and there'd be

24:28.320 --> 24:31.000
a shaft of light.
And then we'd know.

24:32.760 --> 24:35.720
Yeah. And you and me would both know
it was nearly done.

24:39.440 --> 24:41.040
That's where we are now, Arthur.

24:43.360 --> 24:45.040
Just a few more yards to go.

24:47.680 --> 24:49.280
Then you'll change your ways.

24:52.840 --> 24:55.080
And I'll change the fucking world.

25:08.440 --> 25:14.480
In the moss

25:14.480 --> 25:21.240
In the dark

25:21.240 --> 25:27.240
From the start

25:27.240 --> 25:34.120
near the cloud of you

