31:08.000 --> 31:09.520
Did it break?

31:09.520 --> 31:11.160
Mum will fix it for you.

31:11.160 --> 31:13.120
GLASS SHATTERS

31:13.120 --> 31:19.120
or black and white, bird?

31:19.120 --> 31:20.920
MEN LAUGH

31:23.280 --> 31:28.520
but the feeling is old

31:30.440 --> 31:35.120
shorten the road

31:39.600 --> 31:45.640
love was wrong

31:53.560 --> 31:59.120
fathom, blackbird

32:02.720 --> 32:08.160
I fear and I long

32:10.000 --> 32:14.880
shorten the road

32:31.120 --> 32:32.640
GUN FIRES

32:38.880 --> 32:44.920
and show me a song

32:52.680 --> 32:58.240
bird?

33:02.600 --> 33:08.640
dream alone

33:26.880 --> 33:29.280
She's not here any more.

33:47.040 --> 33:50.080
Mr Shelby. No, please, no
condolences.

33:50.080 --> 33:51.480
Thank you all for coming.

33:53.040 --> 33:54.480
Now, let's try to find out

33:54.480 --> 33:56.840
how this new world of ours will
look, shall we?

34:03.680 --> 34:06.240
Perhaps, Mr Mosley, we can turn to
what practical things

34:06.240 --> 34:10.600
Mr Nelson can do to further our
cause, while he's in the country.

34:10.600 --> 34:14.120
